data.enText: any of the curved bones that are connected to the spine and surround the chest

data.chText: 折断的 / 挫伤的 / 开裂的肋骨

data.enText: Stop poking me in the ribs !
a piece of meat with one or more bones from the ribs of an animal
a curved piece of wood, metal or plastic that forms the frame of a boat, roof, etc. and makes it stronger
a way of knitting that produces a pattern of vertical lines in which some are higher than others

data.enText: to laugh at sb and make jokes about them, but in a friendly way

tr: support resembling the rib of an animal
a projecting molding on the underside of a vault or ceiling
a riblike supporting or strengthening part of an animal or plant
any of the 12 pairs of curved arches of bone extending from the spine to or toward the sternum in humans (and similar bones in most vertebrates)
cut of meat including one or more ribs

example: The satirists ridiculed the plans for a new opera house
The students poked fun at the inexperienced teacher
His former students roasted the professor at his 60th birthday

value.def: Your ribs are the 12 pairs of curved bones that surround your chest.

example.ex: Her heart was thumping against her ribs...
example.tran: 她的心脏紧抵着肋骨砰砰跳动。

example.ex: My face was covered with bruises and I had a broken rib.
example.tran: 我的脸上全是瘀伤，肋骨还断了一根。

value.def: A rib of meat such as beef or pork is a piece that has been cut to include one of the animal's ribs.
Rib is a method of knitting that makes a raised pattern of parallel lines. You use rib, for example, round the edge of sweaters so that the material can stretch without losing its shape.
If you rib someone about something, you tease them about it in a friendly way.

example.ex: The guys in my local pub used to rib me about drinking 'girly' drinks.
example.tran: 我家当地酒馆里的人以前总是取笑我喝“女人”饮料。
